      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your concern, but ibuprofen can still pose risks for people with chronic kidney disease. Even a small dose of 200 mg can potentially cause harm to your kidneys over time. It's always best to avoid nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) like ibuprofen, especially if you have kidney issues. Instead, consider safer alternatives like acetaminophen for pain relief. Always consult your healthcare provider for the best course of action tailored to your specific condition.",
